@NODE Preface_eng "QuoteIt - introduction"
@NEXT Guidance_eng
@PREV Overview_eng

  ================
    Introduction
  ================

  "@{B}QuoteIt@{UB}" was written for those who are just ONLINE-users
  in a BBS and not being a point.
  This neat little tool gives you the possibility to quote
  any mail you received at a low expense.
  
  This guide was translated into English by  
  Sascha Reichert (putzi@nightbbs.insider.org).
    
  System-requirements: AMIGA OS 2.0 (V36) and better.
@ENDNODE

@NODE Guidance_eng "How to use QuoteIt"
@NEXT Versions_eng
@PREV Preface_eng

  ==============
    How to use
  ==============

  @{B}QuoteIt@{UB}
  -------
  Format     @{B}QuoteIt@{UB} <textfile> <quote-pattern> [TO <destination file>]
  Templates  FILE/A,QUOTE/A,TO/K
  Path       C:

  The parameter FILE hands the name of the textfile to be quoted
  over to "@{B}QuoteIt@{UB}".
  
  The <quote-pattern> is the string to be inserted at the
  beginning of each line. Commonly, this string contains the
  initials of the quoted person, and is followed by "> ".
  
  In order not to overwrite the source textfile, you can enter
  the argument "TO" followed by the name of the destination file.
  
  @{I}@{U}An example,@{UI}@{UU}
            @{B}QuoteIt@{UB} "Hello.txt" "HB> "

            This example will quote a person called "Hein Bloed"
            using the textfile "Hello.txt" with pattern "HB> "
            

            @{B}QuoteIt@{UB} "Hello.txt" @{B}TO@{UB} "Hello.txt.quote" "HB> "

            The same result, except for the source file remaining
            untouched because of quoting into another file,
            "Hello.txt.quote".
@ENDNODE

